===ACT===


==New installation:== 

1. Run the sql file database.sql:

$ mysql -p -u[user] < install/database.sql

2. In Apache; enable rewrite_module (/etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf) if it is not enabled yet:

LoadModule rewrite_module modules/mod_rewrite.so

3. Edit act_apache.conf, replacing 'act' with the actual installation directory in your web server's DocumentRoot
   Optionally, edit the listener configuration to enable a remote SMS gateway to direct messages to this server

4. Copy the configuration file act_apache.conf to Apache's configuration dir (/etc/httpd/conf.d), with a name that identifies your instance (e.g. my_act.conf)

5. Get apache to reload its configuration:

$ service httpd reload

6. Edit [install_dir]/app/webroot/.htaccess and adjust the path on the RewriteBase command:

RewriteBase /act

7. Create and Edit [install_dir]/app/webroot/index.php

Copy [install_dir]/app/webroot/index.php-default to [install_dir]/app/webroot/index.php

In [install_dir]/app/webroot/index.php, find this line:

define('CAKE_CORE_INCLUDE_PATH', DS . 'var' . DS . 'www' . DS . 'html' . DS . 'act');

And replace the name of the default installation directory, if needed.

8. Copy [install_dir]/app/config/database.php-default to [install_dir]/app/config/database.php . Edit [install_dir]/app/config/database.php, and enter the correct database, username, and password.

9. Copy [install_dir]/app/config/options.php-default to [install_dir]/app/config/options.php

10. Copy [install_dir]/listener/http_post_listener.php-default to [install_dir]/listener/http_post_listener.php

In [install_dir]/listener/http_post_listener.php

modify $processor variable to point to the correct SMS message processor (parser)
modify the gateway parameters for Clickatell (if using a different gateway, see how file_get_contents() is being invoked)
- look for "Clickatell gateway parameters" and "Select gateway/API parameters to use".

11. Set permissions to files and directories, the easiest way is executing:

$ .install/fix_permissions.sh

12. Change passwords (see below for default passwords)

==Update an existing installation: ==

1. Find the schema version of your installation

TO BE COMPLETED

2. Run the sql update files from your current version to the latest version:

$ mysql -p -u[user] < install/dbupdate_v[current]_v[next].sql

To be completed...

==Default accounts and passwords==

admin: adminpass
moderator: modpass
user: userpass
